<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SANTA MONICA; RESTAURATEUR, 37, FOUND GUILTY OF RAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROL CHASTANG 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An owner of A Votre Sante, a trendy Westside restaurant chain, has been found 
guilty of raping a woman he had hired to decorate the firm's newest outlet. 
</P>
<P>
 Nour Tillo, 37, faces up to 16 years in prison when he is sentenced April 21 
in Santa Monica Superior Court. 
</P>
<P>
 Tillo is one of three partners in the A Votre Sante chain of four health food 
restaurants: in Santa Monica, Brentwood, Venice and on La Brea Avenue near 
Hancock Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputy Dist. Atty. Mary Hanlon said the 26-year-old victim is a graduate art 
student and former waitress in the Venice restaurant whom Tillo had asked to 
decorate the chain's Santa Monica eatery. 
</P>
<P>
 Tillo was found guilty last Thursday after a jury deliberated for a day. He 
remains in the Los Angeles County jail in lieu of $350,000 bail. 
</P>
<P>
 Hanlon said the woman was raped in Tillo's Venice apartment last February. 
Tillo and the victim went there to retrieve car keys she had left there before 
a meeting at a Hollywood restaurant, which he had arranged, to discuss 
business. 
</P>
<P>
 She was treated for bruises the next day at a hospital and reported the 
incident to police. 
</P>
<P>
 Mark Gottesman, Tillo's attorney, said his client was innocent and that Tillo 
and the victim had consensual sex. 
</P>
<P>
 At a previous meeting, Tillo had forcibly kissed the victim, Gottesman said. 
The woman may not have exercised good judgment in going back to his apartment 
after the first encounter, Gottesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 He said he plans to appeal the verdict. CAROL CHASTANG 
</P>
</TEXT>
