<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRIDE OF THE COAST BASEBALL TOURNAMENT; BREA'S OFFENSE GETS HELP IN TITLE 
VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE WOJCIECHOWSKI, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda continued its assault on the scoreboard Wednesday by defeating 
Santa Margarita, 10-3, to win the Pride of the Coast baseball tournament at 
Corona del Mar High. 
</P>
<P>
 Brea scored 39 runs in its first three tournament games, including 19 in a 
victory over Orange Lutheran Tuesday.But the Wildcats didn't need to flex their 
hitting power against Santa Margarita, instead taking advantage of six walks 
and four hit batters. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Margarita (5-7) took a 3-0 lead in the first inning. Brian Griffin beat 
out an infield single and scored on Mike Penney's home run, his third of the 
season. Craig Harrison doubled and scored on Paul Nicotra's single before 
Brea-Olinda pitcher Steve Trombly settled down to record his fifth consecutive 
victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda (10-2) tied the game in the bottom of the first. Trevor Lords was 
hit by a pitch, Jason Theis' checked swing produced a single to right and John 
Stoddard, unable to bunt, singled to load the bases. Mike Brambilla walked on 
four pitches to score Lords and a double play and an error scored Theis and 
Stoddard. 
</P>
<P>
 The Wildcats took the lead in the third on two runs without the benefit of a 
hit. Stoddard and Brambilla walked and Marc Anspach and Matt Weyant both were 
hit by pitches. Ryan Knuth's sacrifice fly scored Brambilla for a 5-3 Brea 
lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Stoddard put the game out of reach in the following inning with a three-run 
double. The Wildcats added single runs in the fifth on a hit batter, two 
sacrifices and a single by Dan Anderson and in the sixth on a double by Theis 
and single by Brambilla. 
</P>
<P>
 In the third-place game: 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar 11, Costa Mesa 3 -- Jim Houston had three hits for the Sea 
Kings in a consolation game, breaking a scoreless tie with seven runs in the 
fourth. Matt Friend earned the victory, pitching four innings, allowing no runs 
and two hits for host Corona del Mar (10-2). 
</P>
<P>
 In consolation games: 
</P>
<P>
 Century 1, Estancia 0 -- Century got its only hit off the Eagles' Jose Cabrera 
in the bottom of the second when Jorge Frausto doubled. Frausto moved to third 
on a wild pitch and scored the only run of the game on Jose Romero's sacrifice 
fly. Cabrera struck out five in pitching a complete game. James Gomez pitched 
four innings, allowing two hits, to earn his first victory for Century (8-3), 
and Christian Duran recorded his second save. 
</P>
<P>
 El Modena 18, Newport Harbor 10 -- Rudy Maldonado had two hits and three RBIs 
for the Vanguards, who scored nine runs in the fourth to break a 6-6 tie. Brett 
Hlista and Mike Freeman hit home runs for host Newport Harbor (3-9). 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Lutheran 6, Rancho Alamitos 5 -- Paul Peterson had four RBIs for Orange 
Lutheran (3-8), including a game-winning two-run double in the bottom of the 
seventh. Peterson also hit a bases-empty home run in the fourth. 
</P>
<P>
 Victor Valley 8, Bolsa Grande 6 -- Tom Uribe and Jeff Munney each had two hits 
and drove in a run for Victor Valley (10-4). Bryan Baughman had three RBIs for 
Bolsa Grande (5-6). 
</P>
</TEXT>
