<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; FOUNTAIN VALLEY BLASTS TOP-RANKED MARINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fountain Valley took advantage of a five-run third inning to upset top-ranked 
Marina, 7-1, in Sunset League softball Wednesday at Fountain Valley High. 
</P>
<P>
 Lindsey Collins led the rally with a three-run home run for the Barons, her 
second of the season. Collins finished the day with two hits and four runs 
batted in. 
</P>
<P>
 Deborah Harrelson held Marina (10-2, 1-1) to three hits, and improved to 5-3 
as Fountain Valley (6-5-1, 2-0) remained undefeated in league. 
</P>
<P>
 Molly Sinclair added three hits, scoring two runs and driving in another for 
the Barons. 
</P>
<P>
 In another Sunset League game: 
</P>
<P>
 Ocean View 15, Edison 0 (5 innings, mercy rule) -- Kathy Ponce hit a two-run 
home run in the first inning and combined with Sarah Gulla for a no-hitter. 
Tracy Wilkinson added a three-run home run in the fourth and Janee Sansone 
collected three hits, scored four runs and had three steals for Ocean View 
(8-3, 1-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague softball: 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley 2, Laguna Hills 1 (9 innings) -- Jackie Anderson's 
bases-loaded walk in the top of the ninth drove in the winning run for 
Capistrano Valley (7-4). Anderson also doubled in the first inning to drive in 
the Cougars' other run. Laguna Hills (0-4) lost a run in the second inning when 
an extra-base hit drove in one run, but a second runner that scored on the play 
was called out for missing a base. 
</P>
<P>
 Magnolia 3, Mission Viejo 1 -- Cynthia Garcia hit a two-run double in the 
fifth inning for Magnolia (6-5). Tiffany Mercado (4-4) pitched a complete game, 
allowing three hits. 
</P>
<P>
 In Garden Grove League golf: 
</P>
