<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; WITH LITTLE SUPPORT, CONCORDIA'S VIRCHES WINS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Concordia scored two runs in the top of the first inning and added another in 
the seventh to beat host Occidental College, 3-1, Wednesday in a nonconference 
men's baseball game. 
</P>
<P>
 Adam Virches gave up one earned run, struck out four and walked one in 
pitching a complete-game victory.Occidental's lone run came in the bottom of 
the third inning. 
</P>
<P>
 Despite being outhit, 7-4, the Tigers improved to 12-17. 
</P>
<P>
 In other nonconference baseball: 
</P>
<P>
 UC Riverside 11, Chapman 1 -- Jason Smith and Duke Best had doubles for 
Chapman (8-17). UC Riverside is 23-8. 
</P>
<P>
 In golf: 
</P>
<P>
 UC Irvine finishes 13th -- The Anteaters posted a score of 921 to tie 
Washington State for 13th place at the Fresno Lexus Golf Classic. UC Irvine's 
top finisher in the 54-hole tournament at Sunnyside Country Club was Steve 
Holmes, who finished with a 16-over-par 229 on rounds of 76-76-77. Teammate Tim 
Hart finished at 230 and Paul Calbrase shot 231. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine hosts the Anteater Invitational at Coto de Caza Country Club Monday and 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference softball: 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton 6-7, Arizona State 1-3 -- Melissa Hadfield and Rose Garces 
each had three hits to lead the pace the 13-hit attack for the Titans (16-19). 
</P>
<P>
 In the first game, Monica Bagalayos had three hits and Jennifer Mortensen 
pitched a complete game, allowing six hits, for the Titans. 
</P>
<P>
 In women's nonconference tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 CS Fullerton 5, Idaho State 2 -- Kara Kolb, a Titan sophomore, needed 3 1/2 
hours to win her match, 6-7, 7-5, 7-5. 
</P>
