<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA BEACH; RACE TO AID SCHOOL REBUILDING PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Participants in the annual Laguna Beach Classic 10K/5K/1K race will help raise 
money to refurbish Thurston Middle School, which was damaged in October's 
firestorm. 
</P>
<P>
 One dollar from each entry donation will go directly to the school's 
rebuilding program. The rest of the money will also go to help schools, through 
the fund-raising organization SchoolPower. 
</P>
<P>
 The race April 24 is sponsored by Prudential Securities and Orange County BMW 
dealers. SchoolPower expects to draw more than 4,000 runners and raise more 
than $50,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Registration for the 10K and 5K races is $16 before April 16 and $20 
afterward; registration for the 1K is $12 before April 10 and $15 afterward. 
For more information, call (714) 494-3980. 
</P>
</TEXT>
