<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: SWAT TEAM ARRESTS SUSPECT IN SLAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHIP JOHNSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Los Angeles Police Department SWAT team used tear gas early Wednesday to 
capture a suspect in a slaying who retreated into his Reseda apartment when he 
spotted officers coming toward him, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Detectives spotted Hector Rodolfo Mejia, 36, around 9 p.m. in front of his 
apartment in the 7400 block of Louise Avenue, Los Angeles Police Lt. Anthony 
Alba said. 
</P>
<P>
 Mejia went back into the apartment, Alba said, and police spent the next three 
hours trying to persuade him to come out.  
</P>
<P>
 A Special Weapons and Tactics team fired tear gas into the apartment shortly 
before midnight, Alba said, and Mejia surrendered to police about 12:05 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Mejia is a suspect in the shooting death of Jose Napoleon Orellana, 29, who 
was killed Sunday outside his Van Nuys home in the 6700 block of Hayvenhurst 
Avenue, Alba said. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities said a lingering money dispute between the men may have led to the 
7:30 a.m. shooting.  
</P>
<P>
 Mejia, who owed money to Orellana, shot him several times in the chest with a 
handgun, authorities said.  
</P>
<P>
 The victim was pronounced dead at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
 Police issued an alert for Mejia and the gray 1990 Toyota pickup truck that he 
used to flee the same day of the shooting. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities said Mejia had lived with Orellana sporadically at the apartment 
until the day of the shooting. CHIP JOHNSON 
</P>
