<P>
8 HURT AS CAR UNHITCHES FROM TOW TRUCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHAU LAM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A car being towed by a pickup truck came unhitched on the Golden State Freeway 
on Wednesday and both vehicles overturned, injuring eight people, two of them 
critically, a California Highway Patrol officer said. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred about 2:30 a.m. on the southbound freeway just north of 
California 138. One of two women critically injured in the accident was pinned 
inside the Ford pickup. 
</P>
<P>
 Two people were taken to Northridge Hospital Medical Center, and the other six 
were taken to Henry Mayo Newhall Memorial Hospital in Valencia. CHAU LAM 
</P>
