SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; DRIVER FALLS ASLEEP, CAUSING FATAL CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHAU LAM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 17-year-old fell asleep at the wheel and crashed her car head-on into 
another vehicle, killing an 80-year-old Pearblossom man and critically injuring 
his wife, authorities said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The crash at 1:30 p.m. Tuesday on California 138 just east of Pearblossom took 
the life of Henry Pingry. His wife, 69, was in critical condition at Palmdale 
Hospital Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
 A passenger in the other car, Amy Ballesters, 16, of Palmdale, was seriously 
injured and remained in Lancaster Community Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 The teen-age driver, a Palmdale resident who authorities declined to name 
because of her age, may be charged with vehicular manslaughter, according to 
the California Highway Patrol. CHAU LAM 
