<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSBITES: EASTER MEALS AND BUNNIES ABOUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANNE MICHAUD, Anne Michaud is a staff writer for The Times Orange County 
Edition. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Photos with the Easter Bunny are a highlight of the Easter morning brunch and 
yacht cruise offered by Hornblower Dining Yachts. The cruise leaves from 
Newport Beach at 11 a.m., cruises around the harbor and returns at 1 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Buffet items include eggs Benedict, scrambled eggs, bacon, turkey and salads. 
The cost is $29.95 for each adult; half-price for children 12 and under. 
Reservations are required. 
</P>
<P>
 2431 Pacific Coast Highway. (714) 631-2469. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Roger Rabbit, Thumper, and the White Rabbit from "Alice in Wonderland" will be 
among the famous bunnies celebrating Easter at the Disneyland Hotel. A buffet 
brunch runs from 9:30 a.m. to 4 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The price is $34.50 for adults, $12.50 for children ages 4 to 12, and $3 for 
kids 3 and under. On the menu is glazed ham, roast sirloin, fish, shrimp, 
pastas, waffles, omelets, salads, fruit and dessert. 
</P>
<P>
 1150 West Cerritos Ave., Anaheim. (714) 956-6545. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Pascal Epicerie is busily preparing Easter baskets to carry out for Sunday. 
The baskets, which are $51.90 for two people, contain a poached salmon with 
herb sauce and spring vegetables, a choice of rotisserie chicken or rosemary 
grilled lamb, Easter cake and chocolate truffles. 
</P>
<P>
 The baskets must be ordered in advance. 
</P>
<P>
 1000 Bristol St., Newport Beach. (714) 261-9041. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Pony rides, a Dixieland band and Easter egg hunts accompany brunch at the 
Hyatt Newporter Resort on Sunday. The festivities begin at 10 a.m. and end at 3 
p.m., with egg hunts scheduled for 11, 12:30 and 2 on the hotel's golf course. 
</P>
<P>
 The buffet (with omelets, salads, seafood, meats, fruit and dessert) is $27.95 
for adults, $13.95 for children under 12 and free for children 3 and under. 
Prices do not include tax; reservations recommended. 
</P>
<P>
 1107 Jamboree Road, Newport Beach. (714) 729-1234. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Baci Ristorante has invited Markham Winery to pair wines with a five-course 
dinner Monday night beginning at 6:30. 
</P>
<P>
 Among the dishes are avocado with shrimp (with a 1993 Sauvignon blanc), 
polenta and sausage in tomato sauce (with a 1991 Merlot) and veal chop with 
porcini mushrooms (1990 Cabernet Sauvignon). 
</P>
<P>
 The price is $43.50 per person, which includes tax and tip. 
</P>
<P>
 18748 Beach Blvd., Huntington Beach. (714) 965-1194. 
</P>
