GINTER SETS HOME RUN RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fullerton High's Keith Ginter broke an Orange County record Wednesday by 
hitting his 23rd career home run in a 7-6 victory over Paramount in the 
third-place game of the West Anaheim Lions tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Ginter's first-inning home run broke the county record of 22 set by Valencia's 
Andy Ruscitto (1984-86) and Dana Hills' Lance Marks (1988-90). 
