<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE LINE: OC HIGH: STUDENT NEWS & VIEWS; UPHILL BATTLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Recycling is taking a beating at Capistrano Valley High School in Mission 
Viejo, with banana peels and Kleenex often in the red-colored recycling bins 
and aluminum cans in trash bins, according to article in the student newspaper, 
the CVHS Times. 
</P>
<P>
 "In my opinion, students are lazy.They don't want to walk a few feet further 
to a recycling bin," one student said. "The way it is now, the janitors spend 
their valuable time playing mommy," another said about the need to pick up 
student messes. 
</P>
<P>
 The Environmental Club is urging students to take care of the campus, but it 
may be an uphill battle. "If it wasn't for my throwing trash, (the janitors) 
wouldn't have a job," one student said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
