<P>
54 HOURS; SOCCER FUN-SITES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With World Cup soccer coming to Southern California, many people will 
undoubtedly feel inspired to lace up a pair of cleats and find the nearest 
patch of grass that resembles a soccer field. For those eager to hone their 
soccer skills, Legacy Tour '94 -- which is making the rounds to the nine World 
Cup venues across the country -- will be in Los Angeles the first three 
weekends in April.Legacy Tour '94 "Soccer Fun-Site" events -- for all ages and 
skill levels -- offer contests such as passing, speed dribbling and penalty 
kicks; soccer clinics that feature professional and amateur players, and 
entertainment. The four locations this weekend: Hart High School, Newhall; 
Yorba Regional Park, Anaheim Hills; AYSO Soccer Complex, Riverside; and Ferraro 
Athletic Field, Los Angeles (next to L.A. Zoo). The events from 9 a.m.-4 p.m., 
are free. For future sites, call: (800) 386-4694. LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
