<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Ken Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Committee for an Orange County Arts Council, formed in 1989, officially 
has dissolved and a group of local community, business and arts officials is 
working to establish a permanent countywide arts council, according to 
Fullerton Museum Center director Joe Felz. Officials of the Orange County 
Community Foundation, which helps organize philanthropic efforts, are among 
those involved, Felz said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
