<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: PARAMOUNT; 2 SCHOOL OFFICIALS HALT EFFORTS TO RECLAIM JOBS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Paramount school officials who were placed on leave 16 months ago after 
being accused of mismanaging the district's adult-school programs have 
abandoned efforts to get their jobs back. 
</P>
<P>
 Last week, the school board accepted the resignations of Ed Quesada, former 
director of the Paramount Adult Education Center, and Vice Principal Luther 
Martinez during a closed meeting, Supt.Michele Lawrence said. 
</P>
<P>
 Quesada and Martinez had been fighting for reinstatement since November, 1992, 
when the district placed them on unpaid leave after state auditors reported 
problems in the adult school's record-keeping. 
</P>
<P>
 Both men have consistently denied that they mismanaged Paramount's 
adult-school programs and have sued the district for wrongful termination. 
Quesada said he will now focus his efforts on getting a new job, and on his 
lawsuit against the district. The suit seeks unspecified damages, including 
back wages, Quesada said.  
</P>
<P>
 Martinez was not available for comment. 
</P>
