COMMUNITY NEWS: MAYWOOD/BELL; THOUSANDS OF PUPILS TO BE FINGERPRINTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Under Operation Kid Print, children in Bell and Maywood will be safer and more 
savvy, organizers said. 
</P>
<P>
 Operation Kid Print, a free program sponsored by Assemblywoman Martha M. 
Escutia (D-Huntington Park) in cooperation with the Maywood and Bell city 
councils and police departments, will fingerprint up to 20,000 elementary 
school children in the Southeast area, a Maywood Police Department spokesman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 During presentations at local schools next month, police will talk to children 
about safety, avoiding strangers and how to get help. Police also will record 
the physical description, medical information and fingerprints of each child to 
be used in case of disappearance or kidnaping. 
</P>
