COMMUNITY NEWS: MONTEBELLO; TIGHTER POLICY SOUGHT ON SCHOOL VISITORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Montebello school officials are proposing to tighten campus security by 
requiring outsiders to get permission from an administrator whenever they visit 
district schools. 
</P>
<P>
 The new policy regulating visitor access to 27 schools in the Montebello 
Unified School District is to be discussed next Thursday at a school board 
meeting. The proposed policy would require all school visitors to sign in at 
the school principal's office. Violators of the policy would be turned away. 
</P>
<P>
 Faustino Ledesma, director of pupil and community services, said the policy 
would help school officials maintain greater campus security and prevent 
unauthorized visits. 
