<P>
BRIEFLY: INJUNCTION AGAINST DEFUNCT FIRM WON'T AFFECT 2ND COMPANY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A federal judge has determined that an injunction against Turcal Inc., a 
defunct Fountain Valley telemarketing company, does not apply to Resort Condo 
Marketing Inc., lawyers in the case said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 U.S. District Judge A. Wallace Tashima in Los Angeles clarified in court that 
the La Jolla company is not a defendant in the fraud lawsuit brought against 
Turcal by the Federal Trade Commission, lawyers for the FTC and Resort Condo 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The issue was complicated because Resort Condo was an agent for Turcal in 
1992, and the FTC had sued Turcal as a company doing business under three 
names, including that of Resort Condo Marketing. 
</P>
<P>
 Resort Condo is a separate company that is still operating. The FTC closed 
Turcal earlier this month. 
