<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL ; HAWTHORNE; CITY TO TACKLE 2-YEAR BUDGET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT SANDELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hawthorne officials plan to begin work next month on the city's first two-year 
budget. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council instructed City Manager James H. Mitsch on Monday night to 
present a budgeting plan by April 11. 
</P>
<P>
 The city has been operating without a budget since July, more than nine months 
into the fiscal year. Earlier this month, the council changed the budget cycle 
from one year to two. 
</P>
<P>
 Council members said they have had difficulty trying to eliminate a projected 
$1.8-million shortfall this year caused by the poor economy and state budget 
cuts. SCOTT SANDELL 
</P>
